  {
    "@id": "https://ticketpro.ca/event/1685410618",
    "@type": [
      "http://schema.org/Event"
    ],
    "http://schema.org/startDate": [
      {
        "@type": "http://schema.org/Date",
        "@value": "2026-06-10T19:30:00-05:00"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/location": [
      {
        "@id": "https://ticketpro.ca/place/1109493700"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/image": [
      {
        "@id": "https://tprowest.ticketpro.ca/api/v1/resources/1685472511.jpeg?version=1"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/offers": [
      {
        "@id": "_:g2024520"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://ww2.ticketpro.ca/event.php?event_id=7428"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/url": [
      {
        "@id": "https://ww2.ticketpro.ca/event.php?event_id=7428"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "The Story of Creedence Clearwater Revival"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>Step back in time to when CCR was bigger than the Beatles and Stones combined. On June 14th, award-winning vocalist El Niven and his stellar band will transport you to an era when &quot;Proud Mary&quot; kept on burnin&#39; and &quot;Bad Moon Rising&quot; ruled the airwaves. In the hit live production <b>'The Story Of Creedence Clearwater Remembered'</b>, you'll hear all the classic songs, and recount stories of egos, lawsuits, brother against brother, and a band that changed music forever. The energy and vibe of CCR are recreated right before your eyes.</p>\n\n<p>CCR's sound is instantly recognizable. In a three-year span, they dominated the music scene ... hit after hit after hit. They were more than music - they defined an era - they defined pop culture -- Woodstock -- Vietnam- hippies - protestors - war veterans. The way CCR's music registered with people was something we will probably never see again. In <b>'The Story Of Creedence Clearwater Revivial'</b> that incredible legend is told through stories, music, and multimedia. You will hear CCR hits, including 'Fortunate Son', 'Proud Mary', 'Have You Ever Seen The Rain,' and many, many more.</p>\n\n<p><b>About The Artists</b></p>\n\n<p><b>'The Story Of Creedence Clearwater Revivial'</b> features the powerhouse vocals of acclaimed singer El Niven, who effortlessly channels the energy and spirit of John Fogerty. Niven is backed up by an all-star band of musicians with over a dozen CCMA awards between them.  Their unmatched musical talent, coupled with a multimedia display, leaves audiences with an unforgettable rock and roll experience.</p>\n\n<p>'The Story Of Creedence Clearwater Revival': brought to you by <a href='starsandstorieslive.com' target='_blank'>starsandstorieslive.com</a>, the producers of 'Folsom Prison Revisited' and 'The Story Of The Eagles.'</p>\n\n\n<style>\n .location-page-temp {display: block!important;}\n@media screen and (max-width: 600px){iframe{width:100%;}}\n</style>\n"
      }
    ],
